Croatian teenager Iva Majoli recovered  from a shaky start to see off Belgium's Dominique Monami in three sets in the  first-round of the 150,000 dollar WTA Tournament here Tuesday.
The 16-year-old American-based fifth-seed from Zagreb eventuially clinched  a 3-6, 6-2, 6-2 win.
Experienced eighth-seed Lori McNeil of the United States also reached the  second round when she hung on despite a late recovery to defeat Maria  Strandland of Sweden 6-2, 7-6 (8/6)
